# How to Comply with SSCD

Adopting the Software Safety Consent Declaration is simple and demonstrates your commitment to transparent security practices.

## üöÄ Quick Start (5-Minute Setup)

### Step 1: Add the Badge to Your README

Copy and paste this into your project's README.md file:

```markdown
[![SSCD Compliant](https://img.shields.io/badge/SSCD-Level_1-2EA043?logo=shield-check)](https://github.com/yahiagaming495/Software-Safety-Consent-Declaration)
```

### Step 2: Reference the Policy

Add one of these statements to your documentation, website, or privacy policy:

**Short version:**
> "This software complies with the Software Safety Consent Declaration."

**Detailed version:**
> "This project follows Level [1/2/3] of the Software Safety Consent Declaration, ensuring transparent security and privacy practices. [View the full policy](https://github.com/yahiagaming495/Software-Safety-Consent-Declaration)."

### Step 3: Choose Your Compliance Level

Select the level that matches your project's current capabilities.

## üìä Compliance Levels

### üü¢ Level 1 (Basic Transparency) - *Start Here*
**Perfect for:** Small projects, MVPs, hobby projects

**Requirements:**
- [ ] Display SSCD badge in documentation
- [ ] Link to SSCD policy
- [ ] Provide basic contact method for security concerns
- [ ] Acknowledge SSCD compliance in documentation

**Badge code:**
```markdown
[![SSCD Compliant](https://img.shields.io/badge/SSCD-Level_1-2EA043)](https://github.com/yahiagaming495/Software-Safety-Consent-Declaration)
```

### üü° Level 2 (Verified Practices)
**Perfect for:** Production applications, apps with users

**Requirements:**
- [ ] Meet all Level 1 requirements
- [ ] Document data collection practices
- [ ] Provide data deletion instructions
- [ ] Maintain a security policy document

**Badge code:**
```markdown
[![SSCD Compliant](https://img.shields.io/badge/SSCD-Level_2-FFA500)](https://github.com/yahiagaming495/Software-Safety-Consent-Declaration)
```

### üîµ Level 3 (Full Compliance)
**Perfect for:** Enterprise software, financial apps, large user bases

**Requirements:**
- [ ] Meet all Level 2 requirements
- [ ] Independent security review
- [ ] Bug bounty program or security contact
- [ ] Regular compliance audits

**Badge code:**
```markdown
[![SSCD Compliant](https://img.shields.io/badge/SSCD-Level_3-007ACC)](https://github.com/yahiagaming495/Software-Safety-Consent-Declaration)
```

## üìù Example Implementations

### For Open Source Projects:
Add to your README.md:
```markdown
## Security

[![SSCD Compliant](https://img.shields.io/badge/SSCD-Level_1-2EA043)](https://github.com/yahiagaming495/Software-Safety-Consent-Declaration)

This project adheres to Level 1 of the SSCD. View our [security practices](SECURITY.md).
```

### For Websites:
Add to your footer or privacy page:
```html
<div class="security-badge">
    <a href="https://github.com/yahiagaming495/Software-Safety-Consent-Declaration">
        <img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/SSCD-Compliant-brightgreen" alt="SSCD Compliant">
    </a>
    <p>We follow the Software Safety Consent Declaration for transparent security practices.</p>
</div>
```

## ü§ù Join the Community

Once you've implemented SSCD:

1. **Update your project's documentation**
2. **Add your project to our [USERS.md](USERS.md) file** via Pull Request
3. **Share your experience** in our [Discussions](https://github.com/yahiagaming495/Software-Safety-Consent-Declaration/discussions)

## üîç Verify Compliance

To verify a project's SSCD compliance:

1. Check for the SSCD badge in their documentation
2. Verify they link to the SSCD policy  
3. Review their security practices against their claimed level
4. [Report issues](https://github.com/yahiagaming495/Software-Safety-Consent-Declaration/issues) for any discrepancies

---

*Need help? [Open an issue](https://github.com/yahiagaming495/Software-Safety-Consent-Declaration/issues) or start a [discussion](https://github.com/yahiagaming495/Software-Safety-Consent-Declaration/discussions)!*
